ding Eva to Kare Kano fans.', "Lots of biblical references that don't contribute to anything in the show", "Ryvius and Evangelion at their core are psychological sci-fi about teenagers put into harms way and their slow descent into madness over it. Clearly Ryvius took a thorough look at Evangelion's plot elements and character designs, but doesn't go as far as to fully clone it. There are a lot of shared elements nevertheless: mechas, a mysterious and extremely powerful threat from space, shitloads of teenage angst, a the-end-justifies-the-means government agency who put research progress over the life of people, and of course a lingering end of the world threat. Ryvius unlike Evangelion lacks religious and supernatural elements and tries hard to remain a hard sci-fi and space opera. If you like to see teenager minds melting under pressure, watch both."]

